{"title":"HipoacusiaSubita iPad","guid":"","filepath":"/Users/criaah/Vault/📚 Resources/Mapas-Mentales/Entidades clínicas/Otorrinolaringología/HipoacusiaSubita iPad.smmx","root":{"id":"0","parent":"-1","text":"Hipoacusia Subita\\NNeurosensorial\\N(HSNS)","guid":"qHp2F8hohAz9JV21ha8FWA","children":[{"id":"1","parent":"0","text":"Definicion y Criterios\\NDiagnosticos","guid":"--Dj27c-bhEewV-s-DNgWQ","children":[{"id":"2","parent":"1","text":"Perdida auditiva neurosensorial >= 30 dB","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"3","parent":"1","text":"En 3 frecuencias audiometricas contiguas","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"4","parent":"1","text":"Instauracion en <= 72 horas","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"5","parent":"1","text":"Sinonimos: sordera subita, SSNHL (sudden sensorineural hearing loss)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"6","parent":"1","text":"IDIOPATICA en >90% de los casos (ISSNHL)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"7","parent":"1","text":"Diagnostico de exclusion → descartar causas secundarias","guid":"ax7DrUB380DovBxX0oPUJw","children":[]}]},{"id":"8","parent":"0","text":"Epidemiologia","guid":"","children":[{"id":"9","parent":"8","text":"Incidencia: 5-27 por 100.000 personas/ano","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"10","parent":"8","text":"~66.000 casos nuevos/ano en EE.UU.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"11","parent":"8","text":"Pico de incidencia: 5a-6a decada de vida","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"12","parent":"8","text":"Sin predominio claro de sexo","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"13","parent":"8","text":"Unilateral en >95% de los casos","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"14","parent":"8","text":"Recuperacion espontanea parcial o total en ~65% sin tratamiento","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"15","parent":"8","text":"Adulto mayor: incidencia\\Naumentada con envejecimiento","guid":"2_aguB9g-0LSXJEaKuq4WA","children":[{"id":"16","parent":"15","text":"Estudio geriatrico: mejoria auditiva 65% en >65 anos vs 58% en 55-64 anos","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"17","parent":"