":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"164","parent":"150","text":"EVALUACION PREVIA\\NAL TRATAMIENTO","guid":"YuMgYvD5DiEEY3a2zUvAjw","children":[{"id":"165","parent":"164","text":"Revision de polifarmacia:\\Ninteracciones con corticoides","guid":"pwSvPAiPTKNAc2lFsb-EUQ","children":[{"id":"166","parent":"165","text":"Anticoagulantes: riesgo hemorragico con AINEs","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"167","parent":"165","text":"Hipoglicemiantes: ajuste de dosis durante corticoterapia","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"168","parent":"165","text":"Corticoides previos cronicos: insuficiencia suprarrenal relativa","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"169","parent":"164","text":"Estado funcional basal: determina tolerancia al tratamiento","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"170","parent":"164","text":"Comorbilidades descompensadas: evaluar antes de iniciar","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"171","parent":"150","text":"COMUNICACION\\NY SOPORTE","guid":"msEJXNkgr96agd4ZAnMzhg","children":[{"id":"172","parent":"171","text":"Informar al paciente y familia: pronostico, opciones, limitaciones","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"173","parent":"171","text":"Hipoacusia subita en AM → impacto emocional severo (miedo, catastrofismo)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"174","parent":"171","text":"Consejeria sobre auxiliares auditivos precozmente","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"175","parent":"171","text":"Conexion con fonoaudiologia y audioprotesica sin demora","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"176","parent":"150","text":"SCREENING ORL EN\\NVGI POST-HSNS","guid":"Ax3h3T68lVtim8_zfMozOA","children":[{"id":"177","parent":"176","text":"Audiometria basalmente (si no se ha realizado)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"178","parent":"176","text":"HHIE-S para impacto funcional de hipoacusia residual","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"179","parent":"176","text":"Evaluacion de equilibrio: riesgo de caidas","guid":"","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"180","parent":"0","text":"Diagnostico\\NDiferencial","guid":"9G7Fh53E4I2dTSWaHOB3eQ","children":[{"id":"181","parent":"180","text":"Hipoacusia\\Nconductiva\\Naguda","guid":"-wdXulIrvu3u85NHmWHMDg","children":[{"id":"182","parent":"181","text":"Impactacion de cerumen (muy frecuente en AM)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"183","parent":"181","text":"Otitis media aguda con efusion","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"184","parent":"181","text":"Perforacion timpanica","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"185","parent":"181","text":"DISTINGUIR con pruebas de diapason y otoscopia","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"186","parent":"180","text":"Enfermedad\\Nde Meniere","guid":"Z7qXz0TSZRiSSkdIp49LVA","children":[{"id":"187","parent":"186","text":"Episodios recurrentes de hipoacusia + vertigo + tinnitus","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"188","parent":"186","text":"Hipoacusia fluctuante (no unico episodio subito)","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"189","parent":"180","text":"Neurinoma del acustico\\N(schwannoma vestibular)","guid":"-F_gqEA366uYvIqbfp1jEg","children":[{"id":"190","parent":"189","text":"HSNS como presentacion inicial en 1-3% de schwannomas","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"191","parent":"189","text":"RM OBLIGATORIA para descartar","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"192","parent":"180","text":"Accidente\\Ncerebrovascular","guid":"u0w3Mps-SxS2PTPwvsmKYw","children":[{"id":"193","parent":"192","text":"ACV de fosa posterior (AICA) → EMERGENCIA","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"194","parent":"192","text":"Signos neurologicos focales, nistago atipico, inestabilidad severa","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"195","parent":"192","text":"CRITERIO DE HOSPITALIZACION urgente","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"196","parent":"180","text":"Sindrome de\\NRamsay Hunt","guid":"0Vo4CX_uHiRKbg9pgkXy9A","children":[{"id":"197","parent":"196","text":"VZV: vesiculas en CAE + paralisis facial + hipoacusia/vertigo","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"198","parent":"196","text":"Tratamiento: aciclovir EV + corticoides → URGENTE","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"199","parent":"180","text":"Meningitis","guid":"","children":[{"id":"200","parent":"199","text":"Hipoacusia bilateral de instalacion aguda","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"201","parent":"199","text":"Fiebre, cefalea, rigidez de nuca","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"202","parent":"180","text":"Ototoxicidad\\Naguda","guid":"s2RbYE9KB2Sjgh0tAzZSyA","children":[{"id":"203","parent":"202","text":"Aminoglucosidos, cisplatino, furosemida EV altas dosis","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"204","parent":"202","text":"Antecedente claro de exposicion","guid":"","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"205","parent":"0","text":"Perlas\\NClinicas","guid":"Aygv4SthzmovB_w_49TCEg","children":[{"id":"206","parent":"205","text":"HSNS = URGENCIA OTOLOGICA → derivar a ORL en menos de 24-72 horas","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"207","parent":"205","text":"Weber lateraliza al oido SANO → diferencia HSNS de conductiva","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"208","parent":"205","text":"NO solicitar TAC de rutina → RM con gadolinio para descartar retrococlear","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"209","parent":"205","text":"Tratamiento en <14 dias maximiza recuperacion auditiva","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"210","parent":"205","text":"Vertigo acompanante = factor pronostico NEGATIVO independiente","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"211","parent":"205","text":"En AM fragil: preferir corticoides IT para evitar efectos sistemicos","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"212","parent":"205","text":"Edad no contraindica tratamiento → resultados similares a jovenes","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"213","parent":"205","text":"HSNS sobre presbiacusia previa → considerar como urgencia funcional mayor","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"214","parent":"205","text":"ACV de fosa posterior puede debutar como HSNS → buscar signos neurologicos","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"215","parent":"205","text":"Neurinoma acustico en 1-3% de casos → RM SIEMPRE en seguimiento","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"216","parent":"205","text":"Recuperacion espontanea posible hasta 30 dias → no confundir con exito terapeutico","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"217","parent":"205","text":"Audifono precoz si hipoacusia residual → no esperar meses en AM","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"218","parent":"0","text":"VER\\NTAMBIEN","guid":"ROT5_mb3CrrtAyxl4KgoHQ","children":[{"id":"219","parent":"218","text":"→ Presbiacusia (Modulo 2 - El Oido que Envejece)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"220","parent":"218","text":"→ Vertigo Posicional Paroxistico Benigno (VPPB)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"221","parent":"218","text":"→ Enfermedad de Meniere (Vestibular)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"222","parent":"218","text":"→ Neuritis Vestibular (Vestibular)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"223","parent":"218","text":"→ Sindrome de Ramsay Hunt (Oido Externo)","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"224","parent":"0","text":"Referencias","guid":"","children":[{"id":"225","parent":"224","text":"1. Chandrasekhar SS, et al. Clinical Practice Guideline: Sudden Hearing Loss (Update). Otolaryngol Head Neck Surg. 2019;161(1_suppl):S1-S45. doi:10.1177/0194599819859885","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"226","parent":"224","text":"2. Kitoh R, et al. Clinical practice guidelines for the diagnosis and management of acute sensorineural hearing loss. Auris Nasus Larynx. 2024;51(4):811-821. doi:10.1016/j.anl.2024.06.004","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"227","parent":"224","text":"3. Murray DH, Fagan PA, Ryugo DK. Idiopathic sudden sensorineural hearing loss: A critique on corticosteroid therapy. Hear Res. 2022;422:108565. doi:10.1016/j.heares.2022.108565","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"228","parent":"224","text":"4. Chrysouli K, et al. Effectiveness of intratympanic steroid injection in addition to systemic corticosteroids in ISSNHL. Am J Otolaryngol. 2023;44(4):103872. doi:10.1016/j.amjoto.2023.103872","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"229","parent":"224","text":"5. Zhang BY, Young YH. Geriatric sudden deafness. Am J Otolaryngol. 2021;42(4):102985. doi:10.1016/j.amjoto.2021.102985","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"230","parent":"224","text":"6. Son HJ, et al. Effect of Herpes Zoster Treatment and Sudden Sensorineural Hearing Loss. Medicina (Kaunas). 2023;59(4):808. doi:10.3390/medicina59040808","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"231","parent":"224","text":"7. Swachia K, Sharma D, Singh J. Efficacy of oral vs. intratympanic corticosteroids in sudden sensorineural hearing loss. J Basic Clin Physiol Pharmacol. 2016;27(4):371-7. doi:10.1515/jbcpp-2015-0112","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"232","parent":"224","text":"8. Bareiss A, Nieman CL, Emmett SD. Otolaryngology in Older Adults. En: Brocklehurst's Textbook of Geriatric Medicine. Cap. 12.","guid":"","children":[]}]}]},"node_count":232,"relations":[],"cross_references":[],"specialty":"ORL","folder":"Entidades clínicas/Otorrinolaringología","filename":"HipoacusiaSubita iPad","id":"map_1565","resolved_references":[],"title_raw":"HipoacusiaSubita iPad"}